{%- comment -%}
  ================================================================================
  MALLEM LANGUAGE SWITCHER - DESKTOP DROPDOWN (MINIMOG PATTERN)
  ================================================================================

  Component: Desktop language dropdown selector
  Purpose: MINIMOG-style language switching for desktop users
  Used in: sections/header.liquid (desktop only, ≥990px)

  UX Pattern (MINIMOG-identical):
  - Desktop: Click language icon → Small dropdown appears below
  - Shows: Available languages with checkmark on current language
  - Click language → Form submits immediately to Shopify
  - Mobile: Icon opens drawer instead (unchanged)

  Features:
  - Shopify native localization form (no manual redirects)
  - Details/summary pattern (no JS for open/close)
  - Submit buttons for each language (native HTML form behavior)
  - Current language checkmark indicator
  - Accessible (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)
  - Click-outside and Escape to close (optional JS enhancement)

  RTL: Uses CSS logical properties throughout
  Performance: Pure HTML forms, zero JS for language switching

  Technical Approach:
  - Each language is a <button type="submit" name="locale_code" value="en">
  - Form submits to {{ routes.root_url }}localization
  - Shopify handles session, cookies, redirect
  - Page reloads with new locale

  ================================================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    Get current locale for display and comparison
  endcomment
  assign current_locale = request.locale

  comment
    Early exit if only one language available
    WHY: No point showing selector with one option
  endcomment
  if localization.available_languages.size <= 1
    echo ''
    break
  endif
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  Details/Summary Disclosure Widget
  WHY details: Semantic HTML for toggleable content, no JS needed for open/close
  WHY data attribute: Hook for optional JS enhancements (click-outside, Escape)
{%- endcomment -%}
<details class="mallem-lang-dropdown" data-mallem-lang-dropdown>

  {%- comment -%}
    Trigger Button (Summary)
    MINIMOG Pattern: Globe icon + current language code + chevron
    WHY summary: Native disclosure trigger, keyboard accessible by default
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <summary
    class="mallem-lang-dropdown__trigger"
    aria-label="{{ 'localization.update_language' | t }}"
  >
    {%- comment -%}
      Globe Icon
      WHY: Universal language indicator
      WHY aria-hidden: Decorative, label provides context
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <svg class="mallem-lang-dropdown__icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
      <circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <path d="M2 10h16M10 2c-2.5 3-2.5 5-2.5 8s0 5 2.5 8M10 2c2.5 3 2.5 5 2.5 8s0 5-2.5 8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
    </svg>

    {%- comment -%}
      Current Language Code (EN, AR, FR, etc.)
      WHY uppercase: Common convention for language codes
      WHY visible: User knows current selection without opening dropdown
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <span class="mallem-lang-dropdown__current">
      {{ current_locale.iso_code | upcase }}
    </span>

    {%- comment -%}
      Chevron Icon
      WHY: Visual affordance indicating dropdown
      WHY CSS rotation: Animates when dropdown opens (via [open] state)
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <svg class="mallem-lang-dropdown__chevron" width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
      <path d="M3 4.5L6 7.5L9 4.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
    </svg>
  </summary>

  {%- comment -%}
    Dropdown Panel
    WHY absolute positioning: Appears below trigger without affecting layout
    WHY min-width: Ensures readability even with short language names
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="mallem-lang-dropdown__panel">

    {%- comment -%}
      Shopify Native Localization Form
      CRITICAL: This is the official Shopify pattern for locale switching

      How it works:
      1. Form POSTs to /localization endpoint
      2. Shopify updates session locale
      3. Shopify sets locale cookie
      4. Shopify redirects to return_to URL
      5. Page reloads with new locale

      WHY method="post": Required by Shopify
      WHY action: Shopify's localization endpoint
      WHY return_to: Tells Shopify where to redirect after locale change
      WHY no JS: Native HTML form submission, browser handles everything
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <form
      method="post"
      action="{{ routes.root_url }}localization"
      class="mallem-lang-dropdown__form"
      accept-charset="UTF-8"
    >
      {%- comment -%}
        Return URL Hidden Input
        WHY: Shopify redirects here after locale change
        WHY request.path: Stay on current page
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <input type="hidden" name="return_to" value="{{ request.path }}">

      {%- comment -%}
        Language Options List
        WHY ul/li: Semantic list structure for screen readers
        WHY role="list": Ensure list semantics in Safari
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <ul class="mallem-lang-dropdown__list" role="list">
        {%- for language in localization.available_languages -%}

          {%- liquid
            comment
              Check if this is the current language
              WHY: Show checkmark indicator
            endcomment
            assign is_current = false
            if language.iso_code == current_locale.iso_code
              assign is_current = true
            endif
          -%}

          <li class="mallem-lang-dropdown__item">
            {%- comment -%}
              Language Submit Button
              MINIMOG Pattern: Code + Name + Checkmark (if current)

              CRITICAL: This is a submit button, NOT a regular button
              WHY type="submit": Submits form when clicked
              WHY name="locale_code": Shopify expects this parameter
              WHY value="{{ language.iso_code }}": The locale to switch to

              When clicked:
              1. Browser submits form with locale_code=ar (for example)
              2. Shopify receives POST /localization with locale_code=ar
              3. Shopify updates session and redirects
              4. No JavaScript involved in language switching
            {%- endcomment -%}
            <button
              type="submit"
              name="locale_code"
              value="{{ language.iso_code }}"
              class="mallem-lang-dropdown__option{% if is_current %} mallem-lang-dropdown__option--active{% endif %}"
              {% if is_current %}aria-current="true"{% endif %}
            >
              {%- comment -%}
                Language Code Badge (EN, AR, FR)
                WHY fixed width: Alignment across all options
                WHY semibold: Visual hierarchy
              {%- endcomment -%}
              <span class="mallem-lang-dropdown__code">
                {{ language.iso_code | upcase }}
              </span>

              {%- comment -%}
                Endonym Name (Language name in its own script)
                Examples: English, العربية, Français, 日本語
                WHY endonym_name: Users recognize their native language name
                WHY not english_name: "Arabic" vs "العربية" - endonym is clearer
              {%- endcomment -%}
              <span class="mallem-lang-dropdown__name">
                {{ language.endonym_name }}
              </span>

              {%- comment -%}
                Checkmark for Current Language
                WHY: Visual feedback of active selection
                WHY only if is_current: Conditional rendering
              {%- endcomment -%}
              {%- if is_current -%}
                <svg class="mallem-lang-dropdown__check" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M3 8L6.5 11.5L13 4.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
              {%- endif -%}
            </button>
          </li>

        {%- endfor -%}
      </ul>
    </form>
  </div>
</details>

{%- comment -%}
  Optional JavaScript Enhancements
  WHY optional: Component works without JS (progressive enhancement)
  WHY inline: Minimal code (~20 lines), no need for external file

  Enhancements:
  1. Close dropdown when clicking outside
  2. Close dropdown when pressing Escape key

  WHY not needed for language switching: Submit buttons handle that natively
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
(function() {
  const dropdown = document.querySelector('[data-mallem-lang-dropdown]');
  if (!dropdown) return;

  // Close on click outside
  document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    if (!dropdown.contains(e.target) && dropdown.open) {
      dropdown.open = false;
    }
  });

  // Close on Escape key
  document.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
    if (e.key === 'Escape' && dropdown.open) {
      dropdown.open = false;
    }
  });
})();
</script>

{%- comment -%}
  Component Styles (Scoped Inline CSS)
  WHY inline: Self-contained component, no external dependencies
  WHY scoped to .mallem-lang-dropdown: No conflicts with theme CSS

  MINIMOG Pattern Matching:
  - Clean, minimal design
  - Subtle border and shadow
  - Hover states on options
  - Current language highlighted
  - Smooth animations
{%- endcomment -%}
<style>
/* ============================================================================
   DESKTOP LANGUAGE DROPDOWN (MINIMOG PATTERN)
   ============================================================================ */

/* Container: Hidden on mobile, shown on desktop */
.mallem-lang-dropdown {
  position: relative;
  display: none; /* Mobile-first: hidden by default */
}

@media screen and (min-width: 990px) {
  .mallem-lang-dropdown {
    display: block; /* Show on desktop */
  }
}

/* ============================================================================
   TRIGGER BUTTON
   ============================================================================ */

.mallem-lang-dropdown__trigger {
  /* Reset default summary styles */
  list-style: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;

  /* Layout: Horizontal flex for icon + code + chevron */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.375rem;

  /* Spacing: Comfortable tap/click target */
  padding-block: 0.5rem;
  padding-inline: 0.75rem;

  /* Typography */
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  line-height: 1;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground));

  /* Style: Subtle border, transparent background */
  background-color: transparent;
  border: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.15);
  border-radius: 0.25rem;

  /* Interaction: Smooth transitions */
  transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background-color 0.2s ease;
}

.mallem-lang-dropdown__trigger:hover {
  border-color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.3);
  background-color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.04);
}

/* Remove default disclosure triangle (browser default) */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__trigger::-webkit-details-marker {
  display: none;
}

/* Icon sizing */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__icon {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 1.25rem;
  block-size: 1.25rem;
}

/* Current language code */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__current {
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.025em;
}

/* Chevron: Rotates when open */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__chevron {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 0.75rem;
  block-size: 0.75rem;
  transition: transform 0.2s ease;
}

.mallem-lang-dropdown[open] .mallem-lang-dropdown__chevron {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}

/* ============================================================================
   DROPDOWN PANEL
   ============================================================================ */

.mallem-lang-dropdown__panel {
  /* Position: Absolute dropdown below trigger */
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-start: calc(100% + 0.5rem);
  inset-inline-start: 0;
  z-index: 100;

  /* Size: Min width for readability */
  min-inline-size: 200px;

  /* Style: MINIMOG-like appearance */
  background-color: rgb(var(--color-background));
  border: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.08);
  border-radius: 0.375rem;
  box-shadow:
    0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04),
    0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);

  /* Spacing */
  padding-block: 0.5rem;

  /* Animation: Fade in + slide down */
  animation: mallemLangDropdownFadeIn 0.2s ease-out;
}

/* RTL: Align dropdown to inline-end instead of inline-start */
[dir="rtl"] .mallem-lang-dropdown__panel {
  inset-inline-start: auto;
  inset-inline-end: 0;
}

@keyframes mallemLangDropdownFadeIn {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(-0.5rem);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}

/* ============================================================================
   LANGUAGE LIST
   ============================================================================ */

.mallem-lang-dropdown__list {
  /* Reset list styles */
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  list-style: none;

  /* Layout: Vertical stack */
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.125rem;
}

.mallem-lang-dropdown__item {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

/* ============================================================================
   LANGUAGE OPTION BUTTON
   ============================================================================ */

.mallem-lang-dropdown__option {
  /* Reset button styles */
  appearance: none;
  border: none;
  background: transparent;
  font-family: inherit;

  /* Size: Full width */
  inline-size: 100%;
  padding-block: 0.625rem;
  padding-inline: 1rem;

  /* Layout: Horizontal flex for code + name + check */
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.75rem;

  /* Typography */
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  line-height: 1.4;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground));
  text-align: start;

  /* Interaction */
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.15s ease;
}

.mallem-lang-dropdown__option:hover {
  background-color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.04);
}

.mallem-lang-dropdown__option:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid rgb(var(--color-foreground));
  outline-offset: -2px;
  background-color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.06);
}

/* Active (current) language state */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__option--active {
  background-color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.06);
  font-weight: 600;
}

/* Language code badge (EN, AR, FR) */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__code {
  /* Fixed width for alignment */
  inline-size: 2rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;

  /* Typography */
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.5);
}

.mallem-lang-dropdown__option--active .mallem-lang-dropdown__code {
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground));
}

/* Language name (English, العربية, etc.) */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__name {
  flex: 1; /* Grow to fill available space */
}

/* Checkmark icon (current language only) */
.mallem-lang-dropdown__check {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 1rem;
  block-size: 1rem;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground));
}

/* ============================================================================
   ACCESSIBILITY
   ============================================================================ */

/* Focus state for summary */
.mallem-lang-dropdown summary:focus {
  outline: none;
}

.mallem-lang-dropdown summary:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid rgb(var(--color-foreground));
  outline-offset: 2px;
  border-radius: 0.25rem;
}

/* ============================================================================
   REDUCED MOTION
   ============================================================================ */

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .mallem-lang-dropdown__panel {
    animation: none;
  }

  .mallem-lang-dropdown__chevron {
    transition: none;
  }

  .mallem-lang-dropdown__option {
    transition: none;
  }

  .mallem-lang-dropdown__trigger {
    transition: none;
  }
}
</style>
